WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  Multi_Q is a Workbench game that includes a collection of my
previous 'Q'-games, all in one program. The game boards included
are: Tri_Q, Hexa_Q, X_Q and an additional (bonus) board.

  All the game boards have the same playing pattern: you play by
moving a peg to an empty space, you can only move a peg two spaces
horizontally or diagonally. All the boards feature two playing
mode, a "Normal" and an "Inverted" play:

-In the 'Normal' play, you jump over a peg and that peg will be
 removed. Try to remove all the pegs until only one is left,
 preferably where the empty space was located at the start.

-In the 'Inverted' play, you jump over an empty space and a peg
 will appear there. Try to 'fill' up the board until only one
 empty space is left, preferably where the peg was located at
 the start.

  Have fun!

FEATURES
--------

  -Easy installation: just run the game and play!

  -All game boards can be played in the 'normal' or 'inverted'
